-- ConvergeNet Shares Hit 2-Week High on Talks: Johannesburg Mover
-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 2012-07-31T09:07:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/convergenet-shares-hit-2-week-high-on-talks-johannesburg-mover.html
ConvergeNet Holdings Ltd. (CVN) , a South
African provider of information technology services, rose to a
two-week high after announcing it was in talks that may affect
the company’s share price.  The stock rallied 12 percent to 37 cents, the highest since
July 16, as of 10:45 a.m. in Johannesburg.  “Shareholders are advised that ConvergeNet has entered
into negotiations which, if successfully concluded, may have a
material effect on the price of the company’s securities,” the
Pretoria-based company said in a stock exchange filing today.
“Shareholders are advised to exercise caution when dealing in
the company’s securities until a further announcement is made.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
